Hi all I am having issues building private apps that were building just fine a little bit ago
No changes to the code but the private apps (both with CRM cards) are no longer building anymore
This is an example error:

```--- Quick Setup Card failed to build with the following error ---
[ERROR] Skipping the `PRIVATE_APP` build of `/app` because a dependency build of `/app/app.functions/quick-setup-card.js` failed. View the 
error message for that sub-build for details.

--- /app/app.functions/serverless.json failed to build with the following error ---
[ERROR] The build failed due to an internal error with id `87722c03-f0e3-4b3b-8f0b-cd33858b2f21`. Try uploading it again. If the problem persists, contact HubSpot support with the error id.

--- serverless-function failed to build with the following error ---
[ERROR] The build failed due to an internal error with id `6d7f31f0-94de-4d2e-b567-7cff1b40ae99`. Try uploading it again. If the problem persists, contact HubSpot support with the error id.

--- Quick Setup failed to build with the following error ---
[ERROR] Skipping the `CRM_CARD_V2` build of `/app/quick-setup-card.json` because a dependency build of `/app/app.functions/quick-setup-card.js` failed. View the error message for that sub-build for details.

--- crm-card failed to build with the following error ---
[ERROR] The build failed due to an internal error with id `03e4df4e-a633-4b0a-9e6c-0e09820da157`. Try uploading it again. If the problem persists, contact HubSpot support with the error id.'```
Has anyone seen this as of late?
Looks like something started going on around 1pm mountain

FYI that Amazon AWS is having issues and will result in calls to serverless functions not operating as expected
<https://health.aws.amazon.com/health/status>
We're actively working with them to resolve the situation.
Hi Joshua. This appears to be an ongoing issue with AWS. We're working with their teams to get the situation resolved: <https://HubSpotdev.slack.com/archives/C04A3FUK8HK/p1686685927969979>
